Third-party components
------------------------------------------------------------------------

goodast is a wrapper around the Nuclei v3 Go SDK and other open source Go
libraries. Binaries built from this repository statically link third-party
packages that are distributed under their own licenses. The bulk of these are
permissive (MIT / Apache-2.0 / BSD / ISC). The copyleft / weak-copyleft
components are listed explicitly below for transparency and compliance.

goodast itself is distributed as open source, so the source-availability
obligations of the licenses below are satisfied by this repository.

To regenerate a full, current inventory of every dependency and its license:

    cd worker && go run github.com/google/go-licenses@v1.6.0 report ./...
    cd api    && go run github.com/google/go-licenses@v1.6.0 report ./...

